parts.text:
```json
{
"application": "PyTorch",
"software": [
"PyTorch",
"MMSegmentation",
"Slurm",
"NVIDIA CUDA",
"gcc"
],
"resource_requirements": {
"cpu": 2,
"gpu": 1,
"memory": "32000M",
"partition": "gpu,gpub",
"time": "7-00:00:00"
}
}
```

The script is a PyTorch training script for an object segmentation model. It uses MMSegmentation for training and evaluation. The script utilizes Slurm for job management and resource allocation, requiring two CPUs, one GPU, 32GB of memory, and runs on the "gpu" and "gpub" partitions with a time limit of 7 days. It also relies on CUDA for GPU acceleration and gcc for compilation.
